President Obama held a video conference with President Karzai of Afghanistan to discuss various issues. They talked about addressing insider attacks on US, coalition, and Afghan forces, promoting restraint and non-violence in response to inflammatory materials, and implementing the US-Afghan Strategic Partnership Agreement. They also expressed condolences for the anniversary of former Afghan President Rabbani's assassination and agreed to continue supporting an Afghan-led reconciliation process. The two leaders reaffirmed their support for Afghan sovereignty and agreed to take concrete steps to implement the Strategic Partnership Agreement, such as launching the US-Afghan Bilateral Commission and negotiating a Bilateral Security Agreement.